    <h3 style="color: white; margin-top: 2rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">🛑 The Ultimate Pro-Tip: Punctuation is Power</h3>
    <p style="color: rgba(255,255,255,0.8); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
        If you want your Text-to-Speech audio to sound incredibly realistic and indistinguishable from a real human,
        there is one major secret you need to know: <strong>Use your punctuation marks!</strong>
    </p>
    <p style="color: rgba(255,255,255,0.8); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
        An AI voice engine is smart, but it reads exactly what you type. Humans naturally pause to breathe, raise their
        voices when asking a question, and stop when a thought is finished. The AI relies entirely on your grammar to
        know when to do these things.
    </p>
    <ul style="color: rgba(255,255,255,0.8); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 1rem; padding-left: 20px;">
        <li><strong>Commas (,):</strong> Tell the AI to take a short, natural breath and pause slightly. Use these to
            break up long ideas.</li>
        <li><strong>Periods (.):</strong> Tell the AI a thought is finished. The voice will naturally drop its pitch at
            the end of the sentence and take a longer pause before the next one.</li>
        <li><strong>Question Marks (?):</strong> Tell the AI to raise the pitch of its voice at the very end of the
            sentence, perfectly mimicking human curiosity.</li>
        <li><strong>Exclamation Points (!):</strong> Inject energy, urgency, and excitement into the delivery.</li>
    </ul>
    <p style="color: var(--primary); font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
        The Golden Rule: If you write a massive, 50-word paragraph with zero commas or periods, the AI will speed
        through it in one breathless, robotic run-on sentence. Always punctuate your scripts!
    </p>

